On Tuesday, June 14, 2005, at 05:18PM, Martin Strandgard <mnstra(-at-)unimelb.edu.au> wrote:

>Randall Carpenter wrote:
><snip>
>These distributors on
>these motors are a little stange to me.  As far as I understand it
>the vacuum advance only works in 4th gear and if the temp is 50 or
>below.
><snip>
>The vacuum advance doesn't only work under the conditions you described. 

Actually it does for some models that have the vacuum advance cutoff enabled. See Bentley, Engine & Clutch page 73.

Personally I think this device is bad for the engine. It was a short term emissions addition to make the engine run hot on purpose. Porsches of the same era were tuned/configured hot for the same reasons at the expense of a longer (now reduced) engine life.

